<h2 id="How_to_Upload">How to Upload</h2>

<p>Uploading your data to IU DataCORE is a straight-forward process, but you will need to take some time to prepare
  your data.</p>

<p>Before starting an upload, review the <a href="prepare-your-data">Prepare Your Data</a>
page to be sure you:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Gather all the information you will need for depositing your data</li>
  <li>Meet the conditions for deposit</li>
  <li>Review the <a href="agreement">terms of use of IU DataCORE</a> so that you fully understand your
    responsibilities in using this service</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="Log_in">Log in</h3>

<p>Log in to IU DataCORE to get started! If this is your first deposit, you will need to create an account with
  us.</p>

<p>Once logged in, you will be taken to the dashboard page. In addition to depositing data, the dashboard provides you
  with information about your deposits and account settings.</p>

<h3 id="Describe_Your_Work">Describe Your Work</h3>

<ol>
  <li>From the user dashboard, select <strong>Deposit Work</strong></li>
  <li>Enter Metadata for the data set. The minimum required information for your work includes:</li>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Title</strong> (Provide a descriptive name of the work. What is it formally known as?)</li>
    <li><strong>Creator</strong> (The person, organization or service primarily responsible for making the work.)</li>
    <li><strong>Method</strong> (The way the dataset was collected: equipment used for sensing, survey methodology,
      etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>Description</strong> (May include, but is not limited to: an abstract, codebooks, a free-text account of
      the work, etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>Date Created</strong> (The date the workâ€™s data were created, as determined by the creator.)</li>
    <li><strong>Creative Commons License</strong> (Depositors must choose to apply one of several
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/">Creative Commons Licenses</a> to the data.)</li>
  </ol>
  <li>Select the <strong>Save</strong> button at the bottom of the page.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="Upload_Files">Upload Files</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Read the <a href="agreement">IU DataCORE Deposit Agreement</a> and check the box indicating that you have read
      and agree to the terms.</li>
  <li>On the Files tab of the Deposit form, click on the "<strong>+ Add files</strong>" button and select all of the
      files that comprise your data set (including the documentation files that you have created to provide context for
      your data), or drag and drop your files onto the page.</li>
  <li>Once all files have been selected, click the "<strong>Save Work</strong>" button to submit your work for review
      and publication. The system may take a few minutes to process the changes and update the Work page. You will
      receive an email when file processing is complete.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="Mint_a_DOI">Mint a DOI</h3>

Once you have described your work and attached your desired files to it, contact us (link to form) to request a member of DataCORE staff create a DOI for your work.
<ol>
  <li>Review the information entered and selections made. Look everything over carefully and make changes if needed.
    <strong>Once submitted this information in the minted DOI cannot be changed.</strong></li>
  <li>Once you have described your work and attached your desired files to it, <a href="<%= hyrax.contact_path %>" target="_blank">contact us</a>
    to request a member of DataCORE staff create a DOI for your work.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Congratulations, you have deposited your data!</strong></p>

